\@doanenote {1}
macro:->The
Efficient
Market
Hypothesis
states
that
market
prices
fully
reflect
available
information.
The
form
of
the
hypothesis
depends
on
the
type
of
information
incorporated
into
prices.In
its
strong
form,
prices
reflect
all
information;
in
its
semi-strong
form,
prices
reflect
all
publicly
available
information;
and
in
its
weak
form,
prices
reflect
information
contained
in
past
prices
and
trading
data.
\@endanenote 
\@doanenote {2}
macro:->See
the
preceding
endnote.
\@endanenote 
\@doanenote {3}
macro:->this
usually
happens
when
one
or
more
company
merges
with
another
company
\@endanenote 
\@doanenote {4}
macro:->for
example,
when
a
stock
was
in
a
frozen
state
\@endanenote 
\@doanenote {5}
macro:->PCA
and
wavelet
transform
were
the
most
popular
methods
used
in
literature,
according
to
\citeauthor
{KUMBURE_2022}
\@endanenote 
